<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: PROBLEMS INSTALLING CLASSIC IE]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=3076&amp;p=14402#p14402"><![CDATA[
Classic IE restores the page title and status bar features to Internet Explorer 9/10/11.<br /><br />The Classic Explorer Bar (toolbar) is only added to Windows Explorer, not to Internet Explorer. IE already has a built-in toolbar called the &quot;Command Bar&quot;.<br /><br />The addons need to be enabled for them to work according to the instructions here: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.classicshell.net/faq/#explorer_toolbar">http://www.classicshell.net/faq/#explorer_toolbar</a><!-- m --> The reason the Classic Explorer bar shows up in IE's list of addons is because both File Explorer and Internet Explorer share the same architecture for add-ons.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Tue Aug 12, 2014 1:59 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
